ma Canada|Alma]], [[Nova Scotia]] (1971-2014)\n* [[Maple Leaf Village]], [[Niagara Falls, Ontario]] (1979\u20131992)\n*[[Mill River Fun Park]], [[Mill River Canada|Mill River]], [[Prince Edward Island]]\n*[[Never Never Land Canada Amusement Park|Never Never Land]], [[Leeds and the Thousand Islands|Hill Island]], [[Ontario]] (1967\u20131980)\n* [[Ontario Place (theme park)|Ontario Place]], [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]] (1971\u20132011)\n*[[Pyramid Place Canada Amusement Park|Pyramid Place]], [[Niagara Falls, Ontario]] (1979-1983)<ref>http://cec.chebucto.org/ClosPark/Pyramid.html</ref>\n*[[Rainbow Valley Canada Amusement Park|Rainbow Valley]], [[Cavendish, Prince Edward Island|Cavendish]], [[Prince Edward Island]] (1969\u20132005)\n*[[Scarboro Beach Amusement Park]], [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]] (1907\u20131925)\n* [[Sunnyside Amusement Park]], [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]] (1922\u20131955)\n*[https://www.acrosstheblueplanet.com/blog/trinity-loop/2018/1/11 Trinity Loop], [[Trinity Canada|Trinity]], [[Newfoundland and Labrador|Newfoundland]] (1900s-2004)\n\n===Mexico===\n====Mexico City====\n*[[Plaza Show Mexico City Amusement Park|Plaza Show]], [[Lago de Guadalupe]], [[Dinosaur Park]] is now a university, [[UVM Mexico|UVM]] [[Lago de Guadalupe]] (1980\u20131989)\n\n====Monterrey====\n*[[Mundo de Adeveras]] (2005\u20132009)\n\n===United States of America===\n{{Main|List of defunct amusement parks in the United States}}\n\n==Oceania==\n[[File:Sega-world.gif|thumb|right|The [[SegaWorld Sydney]] building in 1998, Sydney]]\n[[File:Robsons figure eight st kilda.jpg|thumb|right|Robson's Figure Eight in 1908. [[Dreamland (Melbourne amusement park)|Dreamland]], St. Kilda, Victoria]]\n[[File:Leasurelandpic2.jpg|thumb|right|The roller coaster at [[Leisureland Fair]], Langwarrin, Victoria]]\n[[File:Wobbies World Helicopter Monorail and Airplane.jpg|thumb|right|A scene at [[Wobbies World]], Nunawading, Victoria]]\n[[File:Atlanis Marine Park 2, 2012.jpg|thumb|right|The King Neptune statue in 201