aulo|PlayCenter]], [[Barra Funda (district of S\u00e3o Paulo)|Barra Funda, S\u00e3o Paulo]]<ref>[http://www.playcenter.com.br/home.php/ PlayCenter]</ref> (1973-2012)\n* [[Luna Park#In South America|Luna Park]], [[Rio de Janeiro, Brazil|Rio de Janeiro]] (?-2006)\n* [[Terra Encantada]], [[Barra da Tijuca]], [[Rio de Janeiro, Brazil|Rio de Janeiro]] (1998-2010)\n*[[Tivoli Parque]], [[Rio de Janeiro, Brazil|Rio de Janeiro]] (1973-1995)\n\n===Peru===\n* [[Luna Park#In South America|Luna Park]], [[Lima]] (?-2007)\n\n==See also==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [[Amusement park]]\n* [[Amusement park accidents]]\n* Common names used by amusement parks:\n** [[Electric Park]]\n** [[Luna Park]]\n** [[White City (amusement parks)|White City]]\n* [[List of amusement parks]]\n* [[List of closed rides and attractions]]\n* [[List of former zoos and aquariums]]\n* [[List of world's fairs]]\n* [[Roller Coaster DataBase]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://livinghistoryofillinois.com/#DEFUNCT%20AMUSEMENT%20PARKS%20OF%20ILLINOIS Defunct Amusement Parks of Illinois] Over 80 defunct Illinois amusement parks: history and photos.\n* [http://www.defunctparks.com/ Defunct amusement parks]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090126115558/http://wbgu.org/amusementparks/ ''10\u00a2 A Ticket: The Stories & Glories of Old Amusement Parks''], WBGU-PBS documentary about 21 amusement parks located in Northwest Ohio since the 1800s\n* [http://www.moderndayruins.com/search/label/Amusement%20Parks Abandoned amusement park ruins on moderndayruins.com]\n* [http://forum.aboutnewjersey.com/showthread.php?t=190 \"Old Amusement Parks\" on AboutNewJersey.com]\n\n{{Amusement Parks}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List Of Defunct Amusement Parks}}\n[[Category:Abandoned amusement parks|*]]\n[[Category:Defunct amusement parks| ]]\n[[Category:Lists of former buildings and structures|Amusement parks]]\n[[Category:Lists of amusement parks|Defunct]]\n", "text_old": "{{short descriptio