a Falls, Ontario]] (1979\u20131992)\n*[[Mill River Fun Park]], [[Mill River Canada|Mill River]], [[Prince Edward Island]]\n*[[Never Never Land Canada Amusement Park|Never Never Land]], [[Leeds and the Thousand Islands|Hill Island]], [[Ontario]] (1967\u20131980)\n* [[Ontario Place (theme park)|Ontario Place]], [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]] (1971\u20132011)\n*[[Pyramid Place Canada Amusement Park|Pyramid Place]], [[Niagara Falls, Ontario]] (1979-1983)<ref>http://cec.chebucto.org/ClosPark/Pyramid.html</ref>\n*[[Rainbow Valley Canada Amusement Park|Rainbow Valley]], [[Cavendish, Prince Edward Island|Cavendish]], [[Prince Edward Island]] (1969\u20132005)\n*[[Scarboro Beach Amusement Park]], [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]] (1907\u20131925)\n* [[Sunnyside Amusement Park]], [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]] (1922\u20131955)\n*[https://www.acrosstheblueplanet.com/blog/trinity-loop/2018/1/11 Trinity Loop], [[Trinity Canada|Trinity]], [[Newfoundland and Labrador|Newfoundland]] (1900s-2004)\n\n===Mexico===\n====Mexico City====\n*[[Plaza Show Mexico City Amusement Park|Plaza Show]], [[Lago de Guadalupe]], [[Dinosaur Park]] is now a university, [[UVM Mexico|UVM]] [[Lago de Guadalupe]] (1980\u20131989)\n\n====Monterrey====\n*[[Mundo de Adeveras]] (2005\u20132009)\n\n===United States of America===\n{{Main|List of defunct amusement parks in the United States}}\n\n==Oceania==\n[[File:Sega-world.gif|thumb|right|The [[SegaWorld Sydney]] building in 1998, Sydney]]\n[[File:Robsons figure eight st kilda.jpg|thumb|right|Robson's Figure Eight in 1908. [[Dreamland (Melbourne amusement park)|Dreamland]], St. Kilda, Victoria]]\n[[File:Leasurelandpic2.jpg|thumb|right|The roller coaster at [[Leisureland Fair]], Langwarrin, Victoria]]\n[[File:Wobbies World Helicopter Monorail and Airplane.jpg|thumb|right|A scene at [[Wobbies World]], Nunawading, Victoria]]\n[[File:Atlanis Marine Park 2, 2012.jpg|thumb|right|The King Neptune statue in 2012.]]\n\n===Australia===\n\n====Australian Capital Territory====\n\n*[[Canberry Fair]], [[Canberra, Australian Capital Territory|Watson]]\n\n====New South Wales====\n* [[African Lion Safari (Warragamba)|African Lion Safari]], [[Warragamba, New South Wales|Warragamba]] (1968-1991)\n* [[Bullen's Animal World]], [[Wallacia, New South Wales|Wallacia]] (1969-1985)\n*[[Dizzyland Fun Park]], [[Salt Ash, New South Wales|Salt Ash]]\n* [[El Caballo Blanco]], [[Catherine Field, New South Wales|Catherine Field]] (1972-2007)\n* [[Fantasy Glades]], [[Port Macquarie, New South Wales|Port Macquarie]] (1968-2002)\n* [[Leyland Brothers World]], [[Karuah, New South Wales|Karuah]] (1990-1992) - currently operates as The Great Aussie Bush Camp\n* [[Magic Kingdom, Sydney]], [[Lansvale, New South Wales|Lansvale]] (1970s-1990s)\n* [[Manly Fun Pier]], [[Manly, New South Wales|Manly]] (1931-1989)\n* [[Mount Druitt Waterworks]], [[Mount Druitt, New South Wales|Mount Druitt]] (1981-1991)\n* [[Old Sydney Town]], [[Somersby, New South Wales|Somersby]] (1975-2003) - currently used for film and television production\n* [[O'Neill's Adventureland]], [[Leppington, New South Wales|Leppington]] - the park only operates occasionally with portable rides\n*[[Paradise Gardens Australia Amusement Park|Paradise Gardens]], [[Cattai, New South Wales|Cattai]]\n* [[Sega World Sydney]] (1997-2000)\n*[[Tomteland Australia Amusement Park|Tomteland]], [[Williamtown, New South Wales|Williamtown]]\n*[[White City Australia Amusement Park|White City]], [[Rushcutters Bay, New South Wales|Rushcutters Bay]]\n* [[Wonderland Sydney]], [[Eastern Creek, New South Wales|Eastern Creek]] (1985-2004)\n\n====Queensland====\n*[[Adventure Parc Australia|Adventure Parc]], [[Tamborine Mountain|Mt Tamborine]]\n*[[Amazons Aquatic Adventureland]], [[Jindalee, Queensland|Jindalee]] - closed down in 2001, the site has since become [[Centenary Quay|Centenary Quays]], a gated community\n*[[Aquatic Adventureland]], [[North Rockhampton, Queensland|North Rockhampton]], [[Queensland]]\n*[[Grundy's Entertainment Centre]], [[Surfers Paradise, Queensland|Surfers Paradise]]\n* [[Luna Park#In Oceania|Luna Park]], [[Redcliffe City, Queensland|Redcliffe]] (1944-1966)\n* [[Magic Mountain, Nobby Beach|Magic Mountain Fun Park]], [[Nobby Beach, Queensland|Nobby Beach]] (1962-1987)\n*[[Marineland Queensland Amusement Park|Marineland]], [[Main Beach, Queensland|Main Beach, Gold Coast]]\n*[[Mirage Grand Prix]], [[Oxley, Queensland|Oxley]]\n*[[Nostalgia Town]], [[Pacific Paradise, Queensland|Pacific Paradise]], [[Sunshine Coast, Queensland|Sunshine Coast]]\n*[[Olympia Theme Park]], [[Alexandra Headland, Queensland|Alexandra Headland]], [[Sunshine Coast, Queensland|Sunshine Coast]]\n*[[Top's Amusement]], [[The Myer Centre, Brisbane|Brisbane Myer Centre]] - was on the top floor of [[Queen Street's Myer Centre]]; included a roller coaster, a swinging pirate ship and bumper cars. Was deconstructed in 2000 to become the site for [[Event Cinemas]]\n\n====South Australia====\n* [[Dazzleland, Adelaide|Dazzleland]], [[Myer Centre, Adelaide|Adelaide Myer Centre]] (1991-1998) - located on the top floor of [[Rundle Mall's Myer Centre]] was a roller coaster, along with many other activities including a ball crawl\n* [[Luna Park Glenelg|Luna Park]], [[Glenelg, South Australia|Glenelg]] (1930-1935) - the rides for this park were sent to Luna Park in [[Sydney]] upon its closure\n* [[Magic Mountain, Glenelg|Magic Mountain]], [[Glenelg, South Australia|Glenelg]] (1982-2004) - this popular park boasted four waterslides built into an artificial mountain; has since been demolished as part of a redevelopment of the foreshore and replaced by a new park called [[The Beachouse]]\n*[[Puzzle Park]], [[Murray Bridge, South Australia|Murray Bridge]] - adjacent to the [[Callington, South Australia|Callington]] exit on the [[Pacific Motorway (Brisbane\u2013Brunswick Heads)|South East Freeway]]; now closed although many items of equipment still remain on the site<ref>http://www.weekendnotes.com/puzzle-park-adelaide/</ref>\n\n====Tasmania====\n* [[Hobart Zoo]], also known as the [[Beaumaris Zoo]], [[Hobart, Tasmania|Hobart]] (1895-1937)\n*[[Serendipity Park]], [[Devonport, Tasmania|Devonport]]\n*[[Gumbles Tasmania Amusement Park|Gumbles]], [[Richmond, Tasmania|Richmond]]\n\n====Victoria====\n*[[African Lion Safari Victoria|African Lion Safari]], [[Rockbank, Victoria|Rockbank]]\n*[[Alpine Toboggan Park]], [[Whittlesea, Victoria|Whittlesea]] - expanded and renamed [[Funfields]]; original toboggan runs still in existence and best waterpark in Victoria\n* [[Dinosaur World (Creswick)|Dinosaur World]], [[Creswick, Victoria|Creswick]] (1982-2002)\n* [[Dreamland (Melbourne amusement park)|Dreamland]], [[St Kilda, Victoria|St Kilda]] (1906-1909) - the park's Figure Eight rollercoaster remained in operation until 1914; the site is home to [[Luna Park, Melbourne]] today\n* [[Hi-Lite Park]], [[Geelong, Victoria|Geelong]] (1956-1985)\n*[[Kinkuna Country Fun and Fauna Park]], [[Lakes Entrance, Victoria|Lakes Entrance]]\n* [[Leisureland Fair]], [[Langwarrin, Victoria|Langwarrin]] (1984-1992)\n*[[Rosebud Fun and Picnic Park]], [[Rosebud, Victoria|Rosebud]]\n*[[The Swagmans Hat Amusement Park]], [[Corinella, Victoria|Corinella]]\n*[[Whistle Stop Amusement Park]], [[Frankston, Victoria|Frankston]]\n*[[Wirth's Olympia Circus]], [[Melbourne, Victoria|Melbourne]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.emelbourne.net.au/biogs/EM01628b.htm|title=Wirth's Circus|last=St Leon|first=Mark|website=eMelbourne.net.au|access-date=September 5, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Wobbies World]], [[Forest Hill, Victoria|Forest Hill]] (1970-1999)\n\n====Western Australia====\n*[[Acton Park, Western Australia|Action Park]], [[Mirrabooka, Western Australia|Mirrabooka]]\n* [[Atlantis Marine Park]], [[Two Rocks, Western Australia|Two Rocks]] (1981-1990)\n* [[Wanneroo Lion Park]] (formerly [[Bullen's African Lion Safari Park]]), [[Carabooda, Western Australia|Carabooda]]<ref>[https://creditorwatch.com.au/express/asic/organisation/008742201 BULLEN'S AFRICAN LION